# API client & types

## `src/lib/api.ts` is the only place that talks HTTP
- Keep the private generic `request<T>(path, options?)` helper as the single fetch wrapper. It:
  - reads the token via `getToken()` and attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>` when present;
  - on `401` (unless `skipAuthHandling`) calls `clearToken()` and throws a "session expired" error,
    so admin views bounce to login;
  - throws `new Error(error.message ?? "…")` on other non-2xx, and returns `undefined as T` for `204`.
- One named function per endpoint by intent: `getServices`, `getAppointments`, `createAppointment`,
  `updateAppointmentStatus`, `deleteAppointment`, `login`. `login` passes `skipAuthHandling: true`
  (a failed login is a normal 401, not an expired session). Let errors throw so callers can `toast.error`.
- Base URL: `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? "http://localhost:5065"`. Paths start `/api/...`.

## `src/types/index.ts` mirrors the backend
- Entities as `interface` (`DentalService`, `Appointment`); enums as string-literal unions; request
  bodies as separate `interface XPayload`. Auth types: `LoginPayload { password }`,
  `LoginResponse { token, expiresAt }`.
- Field names are **camelCase** and must match the backend exactly. Services `id` = `number`,
  appointments `id` = `string` (GUID). Update this file first when a DTO changes, then `api.ts`.

## Two kinds of "types" — keep them distinct
- **`src/types/`** = the API/wire contract. **`src/lib/schemas/`** = zod form schemas + their
  `z.infer` types (UI input shape). Map between them at submit time.
